byline.contributor: Aurelien Breeden reported from Paris, and Kimiko de Freytas-Tamura from Brussels. Reporting was contributed by Elian Peltier from Paris, Andrew Higgins and Milan Schreuer from Brussels, and Eric Schmitt from Washington.
byline.original: By AURELIEN BREEDEN and KIMIKO DE FREYTAS-TAMURA

abstract: French authorities say they have found third, as yet unidentified body in apartment in suburb of St -Denis following police raid; operation resulted in death of Abdelhamid Abaaoud, Belgian suspected of planning terrorist attacks in Paris, and his cousin Hasna Aitboulahcen; authorities also say Aitboulahcen likely did not detonate suicide vest, as they previously believed.
lead_paragraph: Two bodies had already been identified, including that of Abdelhamid Abaaoud, the Belgian suspected of planning the Paris terror attacks.

headline.main: Third Body Is Found in Rubble of Police Raid Near Paris
headline.print_headline: Third Body Is Found in Rubble of Apartment Where Main Suspect Died
